{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "# Test GloGEMflow with Artificial Glacier Data",
        "This notebook sets up artificial glacier geometry and SMB, then runs the `glogemflow.pro` routines for testing."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 1. Set Up Artificial Glacier Geometry",
        "Define the along-flow grid, a linear bed profile, a parabolic ice thickness, and compute the surface elevation."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; 1. Set up glacier length and grid",
        "xnum = 125",
        "dx = 200.0",
        "x = findgen(xnum) * dx",
        "",
        "; 2. Generate a realistic bed profile (e.g., linear rise from 1200m to 3000m)",
        "bed_dx = 1200.0 + (x / x[xnum-1]) * (3000.0 - 1200.0)",
        "",
        "; 3. Define a parabolic thickness profile (max in the middle, zero at both ends)",
        "thick_dx = 400.0 * (1.0 - ((x - x[xnum-1]/2.0)/(x[xnum-1]/2.0))^2)",
        "thick_dx = thick_dx > 0.0",
        "",
        "; 4. Compute surface elevation",
        "sur_dx = bed_dx + thick_dx"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "### Inspect Initial Variables",
        "Quick checks to verify the bed, surface, and thickness arrays look sensible."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
