    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 2. Visualise Initial Glacier Geometry",
        "Plot the bed and surface elevation of the synthetic glacier before any flow is applied."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; Plot artificial glacier geometry (surface and bed) in GloGEM style",
        "",
        "; x-axis: glacier length in km",
        "x_km = x / 1000.0",
        "",
        "; Surface and bed elevation",
        "surface_elev = sur_dx",
        "bed = bed_dx",
        "",
        "; Create a window for the plot",
        "w1 = window(dimensions = [800, 600], background_color='white')",
        "",
        "; Plot bed elevation",
        "bed_plot = plot(x_km, bed, color='brown', thick=2, $",
        "    yrange=[min(bed), max(surface_elev)], $",
        "    xrange=[min(x_km), max(x_km)], $",
        "    xtitle='Distance along glacier (km)', ytitle='Elevation (m)', $",
        "    title='Artificial Glacier Geometry', $",
        "    /current)",
        "",
        "; Fill area under bed elevation with very light gray",
        "bed_x = [x_km, reverse(x_km)]",
        "bed_y = [replicate(min(bed)-100, n_elements(x_km)), reverse(bed)]",
        "p_bed = polygon(bed_x, bed_y, /fill_background, fill_color=[230,230,230], /data, target=w1)",
        "",
        "; Overlay glacier surface",
        "surface_plot = plot(x_km, surface_elev, color='blue', thick=2, /overplot)",
        "",
        "; Optional: fill glacier area",
        "glacier_x = [x_km, reverse(x_km)]",
        "glacier_y = [bed, reverse(surface_elev)]",
        "p = polygon(glacier_x, glacier_y, /fill_background, fill_color=[180,220,255], /data, target=w1)"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "idl/notebook-renderer",
              "content": "{\"type\":\"idlnotebookimage_png\",\"item\":{\"xsize\":800,\"ysize\":600,\"data\":\"\"}}"
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 3. Define Surface Mass Balance (SMB)",
        "Create a linear SMB gradient: positive (accumulation) at the glacier head, negative (ablation) at the terminus."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; 2. Set up artificial SMB (surface mass balance)",
        "; Example: linear SMB from +1 m/a at head to -2 m/a at terminus",
        "bal_dx = 1.0 - 3.0 * (x / x[xnum-1])",
        "bal_dx = reverse(bal_dx)  ; Reverse to have positive at the head"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
