    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 4. Set GloGEMflow Model Parameters",
        "Configure flow law constants, calibration settings, time-stepping flags, and pre-allocate diagnostic arrays."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; 3. set all necessary parameters for GloGEM flow model",
        "aflow = 1e-16",
        "calibration_method = 0",
        "display_during_flag = 0",
        "display_end_flag = 0",
        "dtfactor = 0.9",
        "dt_flag = 0",
        "dtmb = 1  ; SMB update interval used in update_time_dt",
        "flag_startobs = 1",
        "frontal_length = 1.0 / 4.0",
        "mb_bias_flag = 0",
        "mb_sur_flag = 1",
        "mb_type_flag = 5",
        "nyears = 5000",
        "smb_sinus_flag = 0",
        "ss_criterion = 0.01",
        "start_year = 0",
        "width_flag = 2",
        "smb_method_flag = 1",
        "",
        "; set additional parameters from constants_counters_initialvalues_sizevariables.pro",
        "g_grav = 9.81 ; Gravitational acceleration in m/s^2",
        "nflow = 3 ; Flow law exponent n",
        "rho = 900 ; Density of ice in kg/m^3",
        "",
        "length_fixeddistance = n_elements(x)*dx",
        "df_max = 0",
        "df_lim = (length_fixeddistance ^ 2) / 2",
        "t = 0",
        "if dt_flag eq 0 then begin",
        "    dt = dtfactor * dx ^ 2 / (df_lim)",
        "endif else begin",
        "    dt = dt_flag",
        "endelse",
        "",
        "bed_dx_init = fltarr(xnum) ; Bedrock elevation",
        "df_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Diffusivity factor",
        "fluxdiv_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Flux divergence",
        "fluxdiv_plot_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Flux divergence to be plotted",
        "fluxdiv_plot2_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Flux divergence to be plotted",
        "grad_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Surface gradient",
        "lambda_dx = fltarr(xnum) ; Lambda: angle trapezium describing the glacier cross section",
        "; if flag_startobs ne 2 then begin ; If start from modelled geometry, don't want to set the surface elevation to zero",
        "; sur_dx_init = fltarr(xnum) ; Surface elevation",
        "; endif",
        "term1 = fltarr(xnum) ; Part of the continuity equation (see 'ice_thickness.pro'), also used for fluxdiv_plot, in 'diagnostic_write.pro'",
        "term2 = fltarr(xnum) ; Part of the continuity equation (see 'ice_thickness.pro'), also used for fluxdiv_plot, in 'diagnostic_write.pro'",
        "term3 = fltarr(xnum) ; Part of the continuity equation (see 'ice_thickness.pro'), also used for fluxdiv_plot, in 'diagnostic_write.pro'",
        "if flag_startobs ne 2 then begin ; If start from modelled geometry, don't want to set the ice thickness to zero",
        "  th_dx_init = fltarr(xnum) ; Ice thickness",
        "endif",
        "velocity = fltarr(xnum) ; Velocities",
        ""
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 5. Set Up Glacier Width Profile",
        "Define a realistic trapezoidal width profile and compute per-cell volumes. Surface, base, and mid widths are derived for use in the flow model."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; 1. Define a realistic width profile (e.g., max in the middle, zero at ends)",
        "width_dx = 300.0 + 700.0 * (1.0 - ((x - x[xnum-1]/2.0)/(x[xnum-1]/2.0))^2)",
        "width_dx = width_dx > 0.0",
        "",
        "; 2. Find first ice-covered cell",
        "first_icp = 0",
        "for i = 0, xnum - 1 do begin",
        "  if thick_dx[i] gt 0 then begin",
        "    first_icp = i",
        "    break",
        "  endif",
        "endfor",
        "",
        "; 3. Compute volume per grid cell and surface elevation",
        "obs_vol = thick_dx * width_dx * dx",
        "obs_sur = sur_dx",
        "",
        "; 4. Surface width (copy width_dx, fill gaps if needed)",
        "width_surface_dx = width_dx",
        "for i = 0, xnum - 1 do begin",
        "  if width_surface_dx[i] eq 0 then begin",
        "    width_surface_dx[i] = mean(width_dx[first_icp : first_icp + 10])",
        "  endif",
        "endfor",
        "",
        "; 5. Bed width (for simple artificial data, set equal to surface width)",
        "width_base_dx = width_surface_dx",
        "",
        "; 6. Mid width (average of surface and base)",
        "width_mid_dx = (width_surface_dx + width_base_dx) / 2.0",
        "",
        "; 7. Print total volume for check",
        "obs_vol_total = total(obs_vol)",
        "print, 'Artificial glacier total volume = ', obs_vol_total"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "text/plain",
              "content": [
                "Artificial glacier total volume =   5.68734e+09",
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 6. Initialise Geometry History Array",
        "Allocate a 4-D array `geometry_history[1, xnum, ngeoms, nyears]` to store annual snapshots of surface elevation, ice thickness, and width variables throughout the simulation."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; Set up dimensions",
        "nyears = 100",
        "xnum = 125",
        "ngeoms = 5  ; number of geometry types",
        "",
        "; Allocate a single 4D array: [1, xnum, ngeoms, nyears]",
        "geometry_history = fltarr(1, xnum, ngeoms, nyears)",
        "",
        "; Store initial geometry as year 0 snapshot",
        "geometry_history[0, *, 0, 0] = sur_dx",
        "geometry_history[0, *, 1, 0] = thick_dx",
        "geometry_history[0, *, 2, 0] = width_surface_dx",
        "geometry_history[0, *, 3, 0] = width_base_dx",
        "geometry_history[0, *, 4, 0] = width_mid_dx"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "## 7. Run GloGEMflow",
        "Iterate year by year. Within each year, an adaptive inner time loop calls `update_time_dt`, `diffusivity`, and `ice_thickness` until one full year has elapsed. Annual geometry snapshots are saved to `geometry_history`."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; 3. Run the main GloGEMflow routines (excluding vertical grid update)",
        "",
        "for ye = 0, nyears do begin",
        "  print, 'Running GloGEMflow for year: ', ye",
        "",
        "  ; Set the current time",
        "  time = ye ; get the current time in years -> note the time step within the glogemflow model is smaller & adaptive",
        "",
        "  ; increments time over the current year -> GloGEMflow model runs on an adaptive time step",
        "  while time lt ye + 1 do begin",
        "    ; Update the time and the time step",
        "    @procedures/flow/update_time_dt",
        "",
        "    ; Diffusivity factor calculation",
        "    @procedures/flow/diffusivity",
        "",
        "    ; Ice thickness change calculation (i.e. solve continuity equation)",
        "    @procedures/flow/ice_thickness",
        "",
        "    ; Write diagnostic output",
        "    ; @procedures/flow/diagnostic_write",
        "",
        "    print, 'Time (years): ', time",
        "  endwhile",
        "",
        "  ; Save annual geometry into geometry_history",
        "  if ye lt nyears then begin",
        "    geometry_history[0, *, 0, ye] = sur_dx",
        "    geometry_history[0, *, 1, ye] = thick_dx",
        "    geometry_history[0, *, 2, ye] = width_surface_dx",
        "    geometry_history[0, *, 3, ye] = width_base_dx",
        "    geometry_history[0, *, 4, ye] = width_mid_dx",
        "  endif",
        "",
        "  ; Check for NaNs and other anomalies",
        "  ; @procedures/flow/check_NaN_occurences",
        "",
        "  ; Optional diagnostics -> can be commented out",
        "  ; @procedures/flow/diagnostics",
        "endfor"
      ],
